content.description: Low sit start with hands matched on side pull.  Pull up to right jug, side pull left and easy moves to finish.  Very few moves required but this boulder is the closest to the road and a good warm-up.
content.location: Located on Henry Boulder, a 9-foot tall boulder that is the first from the approach.  Henry (V1) is located on the most uphill side of Henry Boulder with Effie (V0) being just right and around the corner.

content.description: Judging by the cleaner nature of this rock and how close it is to the road, this is probably one of the more historic lines established in this area.  This problem sit starts on left side pull and low right pocket.  Look for the hidden scoop to ease the top out and keep the problem in its grade.
